@fx19880617 I don't think the same code can be reused because the interface needs to be designed very differently so that the plan tree can be returned to the broker.
I want to remove the `PlanNode.showTree()` because I'm going to replace `BrokerRequest` with `QueryContext` in all `PlanNode`, and I don't want to maintain this method (it is already not in-sync with several PlanNodes because of the same reason).
We can re-design the interface when we actually implement the query explanation.

@SudhaGarimella I am not sure how azure permissions work. Things to examine would be:
(1) What user did you run as when deleting the file from azure portal?
(2) what user does the pinot server executable run as?

