1. the azure portal path is mounted into the server, so isnt that like a local file for pinot server?
2. what we did today was we first had used 0.3 release, then did a rolling update (changed the img to 0.4). When using 0.3 you can see we created about 39 segments, when upgraded to 0.4, the first segment it tried to create had failed. So the point I am saying is - same setup worked well with 0.3 release, when v did a rolling update to 0.4, seg creation failed.
